    def click_sidebar_item(self, index):
        """
        Click on a sidebar item by its index
    
        Args:
            index: The 1-based index of the sidebar item
    
        Returns:
            str: The name of the clicked item
        """
        # Get the item name
        name_selector = f"({self.SIDEBAR_ITEMS})[{index}]{self.SECTION_TITLE}"
        name_element = self.page.query_selector(name_selector)
    
        if name_element:
            name = name_element.text_content().strip()
    
            # Take screenshot before clicking
            screenshot_path = f"reports/screenshots/before_click_item_{index}.png"
            self.page.screenshot(path=screenshot_path)
    
            # Click on the name element
            name_element.click()
            self.wait_for_loading()
    
            # Take screenshot after clicking
            screenshot_path = f"reports/screenshots/after_click_item_{index}_{name}.png"
